description.question:
What will the following css rule select?
<pre><code class='language-javascript'>.test > div</code> {
...
}</code></pre>

description.explanation:
eg:  
<pre><code class='language-html'>&lt;div class='test'&gt;
&lt;div class='box'&gt;
&lt;div class='content'&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class='box'&gt;
&lt;div class='content'&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>

Would target only the elements with a class of 'box' as these are the direct children of 'test'.

For example if you wanted all the paragraph tags in a specific class to have the colour blue instead of black
<pre><code class='language-javascript'></code>.myClass p  {
color: blue !important
}</code></pre>

Nothing would appear on the page, the content property needs to be used with sudo elements like <code>::after</code> or <code>::before</code> eg:<br /><code>.testDiv {<br />width: 20%;<br />height: 20%;
}
.testDiv::after {
content: 'add this text'
}</code>
